issues.suggested_fix:
Make the constructor signatures consistent. Preferred fixes:
- If no apiKey is required: change the solution's constructor to match the template (only PersonService parameter). Example: public PersonResource(PersonService personService) { this.personService = personService; }
- If an apiKey is intentionally needed: document it in the problem statement and template, and annotate/configure its injection (e.g., public PersonResource(PersonService personService, @Value("${api.key:}") String apiKey) { this.personService = personService; this.apiKey = apiKey; }), and add a corresponding field and property configuration. Aligning either template or solution to the same constructor signature will remove the confusion and prevent autowiring issues.
